<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-01-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="22" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d22">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 702.5511–30.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Belgian Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Belgian
                                        Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-01-23"><hi rend="italic">January 23,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 64.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that the
                            consular representation of the Congo State having been merged with the
                            consular representation of Belgium, the functions of the consul general
                            of the <pb facs="0096" n="14" xml:id="pg_14"/> Congo to the United
                            States, formerly held by Mr. James Gustavus Whiteley, have been
                            discontinued and that the affairs that were handled by that consulate
                            general are now and will hereafter be conducted through the consular
                            representatives of Belgium in the United States.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Ct. Conrad de
                            Buisseret.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>